There are just 16 days to go until the first race of the season and just six until we see the first cars on track for testing in Bahrain. All 10 teams have unveiled their 2023 designs with Alpine rounding out the launches on Thursday evening. Lewis Hamilton’s controversial Abu Dhabi Grand Prix title loss came to a head one year today as race director Michael Masi was sacked. Masi was axed by the FIA after “human error” was blamed for causing chaos which led to Max Verstappen’s maiden title win. Meanwhile, Ferrari is embroiled in a headache after claims the Scuderia may have stolen Mercedes designs. An expert also said a major feature on Ferrari’s car during Tuesday's unveiling could even be “illegal” and removed ahead of the first race. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE F1 UPDATES THROUGHOUT THE DAY